<TITLE> Atiqullah Khan Masud jailed for seven years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 9 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court Sunday sentenced Globe Janakantha Shilpa Paribar chairman Atiqullah Khan Masud to seven years in prison for fraud. Judge Tanzina Ismail of the Special Judge's Court-6, set up on the Jatiya Sangsad premises, also sentenced Rajuk official SM Asaduzzaman to seven years in jail. The court slapped a combined fine of Tk 7.56 crore on the two. They have to serve another year in jail in failure to pay the fine, according to the sentencing. Atiqullah Khan, also editor of Bangla-language daily Janakantha, is in jail, but Asaduzzaman is on the run. Joint forces arrested Atiqullah on March 7 last year. The Anticorruption Commission on Sept 30 last year filed the case with Motijheel Police Station against the accused for having roles in approving the design of a building illegally. According to case details, Atiqullah submitted a design of a 10-storey building to be constructed on Mirpur Road to Rajuk on March 9, 2000. Rajuk approved a design for a six-storey building. ACC deputy assistant director Md Abul Kashem pressed charges against the accused on Dec 11. The name of another Rajuk official, Abdul Latif, was taken off the chargesheet. The same court on March 6 sentenced the two accused to seven years in jail in another fraud case. bdnews24
